PORT ELIZABETH Three suspects were arrested within hours after allegedly breaking into a home in Westering Port Elizabeth, Eastern Cape police said on Monday.Police spokesperson, Colonel Priscilla Naidu, said that police responded to a complaint of a housebreaking in progress on Monday.READ: SA actor arrested in brothel raid to spend weekend in jail On arrival at the home, police established that a bakkie was seen at the house," said Naidu. While at the scene officers activated their informer network which led them to a house in Wells Estate in Motherwell. Naidu said three suspects aged between 39 and 42 years old were arrested and the stolen property, including jewellery, clothing and electronics were recovered.The suspects will appear in court soon.African News Agency